articles.title: About the Paycheck Protection Program Data Website
articles.contents:
I found it quite difficult to parse the large files provided by the SBA that contained who got what in regards to the PayCheck Protection Program. So, I merged and cleaned the files and then but them into a database so that others could find companies that got PPP loans more easily.
Other sites have done similar things. ProPublica has an excellent site of PPP data. However, we add some value beyond what is currently available:
The data here is newer (by about 5 months, released in December, 2020)
It includes exact loan approval amounts (instead of ranges).
We may include more data. The raw data includes loans under $150k, unlike other sources. However, as is, a lack of computer processing power makes it so that this website only serves up a fraction of the records available – we focus on the largest loans. When I have more time (and can pay for time on a multi-core supercomputer) I’ll add more records.
Note that currently the search functionality is limited. But I’m working to make it better.
So ProPublica is great, and may be more comprehensive. So check them out!
Notes from the SBA
The SBA released some info about the data.
